1 SECTION 7. LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT STUDY - DEPARTMENT OF CORRECTIONS
2 AND REHABILITATION. During the 2025-26 interim, the legislative management shall consider
3 studying the impacts of providing requirements for offenders sentenced to the supervision and
4 custody of the department of corrections and rehabilitation. The study must include a thorough
5 review of the impacts of requiring an offender to serve eighty-five percent of an offender's term
6 of imprisonment in a secured facility, together with input from district court judges regarding
7 sentencing decisions, state's attorneys regarding charging decisions, the department of
8 corrections and rehabilitation regarding early release and use of transitional facilities to provide
9 outside services to inmates, and the parole board regarding decisions to parole an inmate. The
10 legislative management shall report its findings and recommendations, together with any
11 legislation required to implement the recommendations, to the seventieth legislative assembly.
